cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is about object detection using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for object detection, which involves training a single-stage network using Recurrent Rolling Convolution (RRC). This is a machine learning (ML) technique, so cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses multi-scale feature maps and deep context to construct object classifiers and bounding box regressors, which are related to neural networks (NNs) and deep learning (DL), so cs.NE is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the KITTI dataset, which is a benchmark for robotics research, so cs.RO is a possible sub-category as well.
